    "explanation": "Diagram 1 presents a more complex, multi-layered architecture focusing on a CGI proxy system. It includes components for access, proxying, support platform services, and CGI portal functions. Diagram 2 focuses on a simpler HTTP proxy server architecture with clear request handling, filtering, and backend server interaction. \n\nThe key difference is the scope. Diagram 1 illustrates a full-fledged system designed for a wider range of tasks, while Diagram 2 hones in on the internals and core functionalities of an HTTP proxy. Diagram 1 includes components like Redis, Kafka, and MySQL, indicating a data-intensive application, whereas Diagram 2 emphasizes request routing, filtering, and configuration. Diagram 1 includes more layers and the data aspect, while Diagram 2 is more of a proxy handling system. \n\n**Score:**\n- Diagram 1: 8/10 (Comprehensive but lacks clarity on component interactions)\n- Diagram 2: 7/10 (Clearer focus but limited scope). It is good diagram to understanding the proxy system clearly.\n\nDiagram 1 is better because it provides a more comprehensive view of a complex system, even though Diagram 2 is easier to understand."
